# CompliTrace Repository Analysis (Code-Accurate Snapshot)

_Last verified against repository code on 2026-04-21._

## 0) Goal and method

This document maps the current implementation in this repository to the real runtime behavior of the system.
It is intentionally code-first: every claim below is based on files under `apps/*`, `scripts/*`, `infra/*`, and `docker-compose.yml`.

---

## 1) Repository topology

- `apps/ingestion-service`: PDF upload, parsing, section extraction, document/section persistence.
- `apps/knowledge-service`: GDPR chunk indexing and semantic search over Qdrant.
- `apps/orchestration-service`: audit execution, legal gating, publication controls, review/export/report APIs.
- `apps/frontend`: React/Vite UI for upload â†’ sections â†’ findings/review/analysis â†’ report.
- `scripts`: GDPR ingestion + validation + benchmarking utilities.
- `infra/prometheus`, `infra/grafana`: monitoring and dashboard provisioning.
- `data/raw`, `data/processed`: source PDFs + processed GDPR chunk corpus.

