## 6) Audit lifecycle (`services/audit_runner.py`)

### 6.1 Entry flow

`POST /audits` persists `Audit(status="pending")`, runs `run_audit(...)`, and marks failed state on exception.

### 6.2 Pre-loop global setup

`run_audit(...)` computes and/or captures:

- document sections from ingestion
- cross references and source-scope confidence
- document mode (`privacy_notice`/other inferred modes)
- document posture and document-wide duty validation
- obligation map
- effective LLM budget cap

### 6.3 Per-section flow (implemented)

For each section, pipeline includes:

- runtime-budget guard
- applicability filtering (`_is_not_applicable`, `_section_auditability_type`)
- collection-mode inference + candidate issue spotting
- legal fact extraction + legal qualification per issue
- retrieval query generation and mode-aware reranking
- evidence sufficiency gating
- conditional LLM call (`run_llm_classification`) with provider fallback
- citation validation/salvage and legal-fit checks
- deterministic overrides (violation patterns, consistency controls, dedupe)
- finding + citation persistence

### 6.4 Post-loop flow

- notice-level and systemic synthesis
- support hydration for systemic findings
- completeness enforcement
- final disposition map build
- final publication validator
- review/publish invariant enforcement
- suppression ledger recording
- partner review pass
- evidence record upsert
- state invariant validator
- analysis snapshot materialization
- audit terminal state update

---

## 7) LLM subsystem (`services/llm.py`)

- strict JSON contract for model output (status/severity/notes/legal fields/citations/etc.)
- provider adapters:
  - Groq via OpenAI-compatible chat completions
  - Gemini via `generateContent`
- bounded retry handling for HTTP 429
- sentinel path when all attempts are rate-limited
- coercion + normalization into `LlmFinding` model

