## 13) Boundaries and known constraints

- Designed for GDPR transparency-style audits; not a general legal engine.
- Clean text-extractable PDFs are assumed; OCR/scanned-PDF workflow is not implemented.
- LLM output is advisory inside a deterministic gating pipeline.
- Publication path is conservative by design and can suppress borderline findings.

---

## 14) Summary conclusion

CompliTrace is implemented as a multi-service compliance pipeline with:

- deterministic ingestion + structured sectioning,
- retrieval-grounded legal evidence lookup,
- constrained LLM classification,
- deterministic legal/publication controls,
- explicit review and export contracts,
- user-facing sanitization barriers,
- metrics-first observability.

This is materially different from a generic chatbot architecture.
